# Agent room frontend ↔ orchestration doc sync

When you change **visitor-visible copy**, **screen layout**, **choreography chips**, or **routing behavior** in the agent room:

## Copy SSOT

- Screen copy lives in `src/lib/agent-room/data/*-copy.ts` (e.g. `home-copy.ts`), not inline in components.
- Components import from those modules (`home-screen.tsx`, `agent-room-fallback.tsx`).

## After frontend copy changes

1. Run `pnpm agent-orchestration:sync-screen-copy` — updates `docs/build/agent-orchestration/page-scripts/`, `movemental-room-script.md`, and `engine/prompts/room-host.md` from the TS SSOT.
2. Do **not** hand-edit text inside `<!-- LIVE-COPY:*:begin/end -->` blocks in those files.
3. Rebuild the docs viewer if it is open: `pnpm agent-orchestration:viewer:build` (or restart `pnpm agent-orchestration:viewer`).

## After non-copy screen behavior changes

Update the matching plain-English page script in `docs/build/agent-orchestration/page-scripts/` (outside LIVE-COPY blocks) so the orchestration viewer reflects what visitors actually experience.

## Check before PR

```bash
pnpm agent-orchestration:sync-screen-copy --check
```
